  #hub-application(data-magellan-destination='hub-application')
  section.main
    .row
      .small-12.columns
        figure.img-love
          img(data-interchange='[/assets/images/network/hub.jpg, (default)], [/assets/images/network/hub-lg.jpg, (medium)]')

    header.overview-header
      .row
        .medium-3.columns
          h2.section-title Hub Application
        .medium-9.columns
          p Are you interested in becoming a Hub? The Savory Institute accepts applications for individuals or organizations interested in starting a Savory Hub in their region.

    .row
      .small-12.columns
        p We are looking for entrepreneurial, innovative and passionate organizations or individuals who desire to create local solutions to land degradation. Hubs can be an extension of an existing organization or a completely new organization. We encourage for-profits, NGOs, and cooperatives to apply. All Hubs should be financially sustainable through providing local product and service solutions for land degradation, food and water security, and community empowerment.
        p Since 2012, the Savory Institute has received over 200 applications for the establishment of local Hubs — we choose 10 individuals or organizations to become Hub Candidates every year. We have local Hubs or Candidates in over 20+ countries.

        hr

    .row
      .medium-6.columns
        img(data-interchange='[/assets/images/network/hexagon.png, (default)], [/assets/images/network/hexagon-lg.png, (medium)]')
      .medium-6.columns
        h3 Application Process:
        p The Savory Institute will evaluate every application in three major categories: impact, scale, and financial sustainability.  We will narrow all the applications to the top 20 applicants. These top 20 applications will be required to complete the following process to guide Savory in choosing the 10 Hub Candidates.

        ul.application-process
          li
            h4 Interview
            p Every Hub applicant chosen is required to complete a phone interview with Savory team. This interview will be important in making a final decision. You will be given an opportunity to present your proposal for becoming a Hub. We are available to answer any questions about the selection process.

          li
            h4 Hub Business Plan
            p Every Hub is required to submit a final business plan providing the specifics of implementation relevant to the existing region. This implementation will involve managing the local demonstration site, offering holistic training and consulting services, and providing monitoring and data management services for site management.

          li
            h4 Promotional Video
            p In addition, each applicant should provide a short (3-5 minute) inspirational video on why they should be selected as a Hub. We encourage creativity! Each video should include the following key points:

            ul.bordered-list
              li Vision for the local Hub
              li Footage of the local area’s landscape and communities
              li Insights into the people who will be impacted
              li Local challenges and issues
              li Why here and why now?
              li Tell us about your team and who will be leading these efforts

    .row
      .small-12.columns
        hr
        h3 Hub Candidates:
        p After being selected as a Hub Candidate, each individual Hub will begin the process of accreditation with the Savory Institute.

        .key-points
          .keyline
          .row.collapse
            .medium-6.columns.left
              .point
                h4 Demonstration Site
                p Maintain management influence or control of a local demonstration site for the purpose of education, holistic training and research. This site must be managed using Holistic Management. The site must use the core Holistic Management planning procedures for operating. Each Hub will use the local site for providing workshops and demonstrations on how the practice of Holistic Management works on site. The actual farm planning procedures and baseline monitoring must be on file before the organization can be recognized as an accredited Hub. The Hub demonstration site may be audited to confirm compliance of the requirements.

              .point
                h4 Savory Institute Accredited Professionals
                p To maintain quality and consistency amongst the Hub network and special projects, we require that all Hubs use Savory Institute accredited professionals in training and consulting. Each Hub will have access to the network of accredited professionals to provide these services. Each Hub can hire accredited professionals as staff or provide staff to be accredited by Savory Institute or another accredited Hub. Holistic Land Management Training will be provided to Hubs interested in having accredited professionals on staff.

              .point
                h4 Hub Leadership Bootcamp
                p Two leaders from each Hub will be required to attend the Hub Leadership Bootcamp. The typical format includes 8-10 days of training addressing organizational development, brand and marketing support, networking, a Holistic Management overview, and field training and support. The training will be facilitated by Savory Institute staff, including a few sessions with Allan Savory.

            .medium-6.columns.right
              .point
                h4 Funding
                p Based upon the business plan submitted, each Hub will need to raise the financial resources needed for execution. Those resources will need to be confirmed before official accreditation. The Savory Institute will provide assistance in fundraising for grants and investments. Savory Institute encourages each candidate to seek out the necessary funding for implementation of the business plan. We cannot guarantee funding will be available to existing candidates.

              .point
                h4 Fees and Expenses
                p Each Hub is required to provide funding for the fees and expenses of the following activities. In the past, Savory Institute has been able to contribute donor funds to cover the majority of expenses associated with the Leadership Bootcamp. Future funding is not guaranteed and a $5,000 deposit is required. Your deposit covers the expenses of the Hub Leadership Bootcamp (2 people for 8-10 days including food, accommodations, and travel within Zimbabwe*). *International travel to Zimbabwe is not included. Each Hub will make the decision if they need an Accredited Professional as a member of the Hub core team. If needed, Savory Institute will provide a specific training in the first quarter of 2015. This training will be a total of 8 days. The cost is $2,000 and can include 2 people. If an existing team member is already an Accredited Professional this is not needed.

